<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="859" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d859">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Forrestal Papers</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Diary Entry for December 31, 1948, by the Secretary of
                                Defense</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Forrestal</hi>)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-31">December 31, 1948</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="flushleft">
                            <hi rend="italic">Cabinet—China—Palestine</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>Subject this morning at Cabinet was China.</p>
                        <p>[Here follow two paragraphs concerning China.]</p>
                        <p>Palestine:</p>
                        <p>Lovett said the Israeli troops had apparently invaded Egypt.
                            Specifically, they were reported to have attacked an air field within
                            the Egyptian border; that it was reported the British would notify us
                            that the failure of the Israelis to withdraw promptly would
                            automatically bring into operation the Anglo-Egyptian mutual defense
                            pact.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>